<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7836] Data loss after moving tokens</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7836</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The dtest topology_test:TestTopology.movement_test is failing on 2.1.0 and 2.1-HEAD. The test, which has been attached, goes through the following workflow:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Create an unbalanced three node cluster without vnodes&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Create a keyspace with RF=1&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Load data into the cluster&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Flush the cluster with nodetool flush&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Move the tokens around to balance the cluster, using nodetool move&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Run nodetool cleanup&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;At this point, the test checks that all 10,000 of the originally inserted rows are still there. In 2.0.10 that is true, however in 2.1, only ~4000 rows exist.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;OSX and Ubuntu 14.04&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
